ENEL GREEN POWER HILLTOPPER WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Enel Green Power HillTopper Wind, LLC ("HillTopper") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the HillTopper generating facility ("HillTopper Facility").
The HillTopper Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Logan County, Illinois. The HillTopper Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth HillTopper's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the HillTopper Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
HillTopper's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to HillTopper shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $960,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $80,000.00. 1
